 there weren't - there were no betting or swearing or anything like that. I know - I know on a Sunday - a Saturday night they used - these that had these three children, they - they used to - they'd go to different houses or if - I - I should imagine they
 
would come more to our house because they could leave three children you see better and - they used to play whist. I can remember them doing that. And they used to play while twelve o'clock and if there was in middle of a game when it struck twelve they -
 it finished. They didn't - finish it off. No. It was Sunday then. I can al - I can remember that. It didn't matter if the game wasn't finished, they - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1906339\charrsid10379359 they had
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid476072\charrsid10379359  - they - they finished, it was Sunday. A bit much was that but it was so.
