t
 any children and, oh, he used to love us to go and we used to - you know, sit in the street and sing away and - and there was another girl, she sent to the Salvation Army and - and we had one or two tambourines you see and - and before we'd finished, whe
n
 we'd finished always used to bring us all - take us all into the house, did this particular man. He loved children and - there were always some sweet - sweets for us all. They were right happy days. Yes, it was. And you see, they all knew one another and
 
