\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7626777 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid476072\charrsid10379359 What did you do - go to the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11083444 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid476072\charrsid10379359 
Well - this friend of mine, she was three months older than me and she'd gone - she had a sister that worked at the mill you see and so - her sister got her on and and then when she - when she went 
half time well, on the Saturday morning - you worked one Saturday morning and played the other. Now when - when you was playing you - you had to go in for your doffing money. And - and I used to go with her. For her doffing money you see. And it was three
p
ence. That was for yourself. That was your spending money. And so when I was going with her the overlooker asked me when I was - when - when was I twelve. Well she was twelve in the January and I was twelve in the - in the April and so he set me on, see. 
I was set on oh a month or two before I was twelve.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7626777 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid476072\charrsid10379359 What did your parents think about it?
