\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7626777 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid476072\charrsid10379359 Where would you go with your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11083444 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid476072\charrsid10379359 
Well - did you come up Spring Gardnes Lane? Yes, well - that was the walk. From church - where we used to run out as fast as ever we could and - and then we'd to come up Cavendish Street and - then go on a - if we wanted to see
 anybody we knew where to go, they all were - it was place where the - they all have a place, well they all used to have, I don't think they have now, but in those days they all had a - a place where they went. Well they did in Yorkshire, I don't know whe
ther they did in Lancashire and that but - they always had a special place where you could meet boys and girls and - that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7626777 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid476072\charrsid10379359 Did you make any boy friends as well as the girls?
